com.ampro.robinhood.endpoint.authorize.data

Class AuthorizationData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ampro.robinhood.endpoint.authorize.data.AuthorizationData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ApiElement

    public class AuthorizationData
extends java.lang.Object
implements ApiElement
    A wrapper for both possible API login responses. It holds a token String, multifactor auth type and whether multifactor is required for the account.
    MultifactorAuthorization (or Two-factor Authorization) is referred to as mfa by the Robinhood Api. (Robinhood calls it Two-Factor, but the Api calls it multifactor...).
    Since:
    0.8.4
